<taxonomicName id="086A8D4BE92D6B5BC451CDD2FD55E19F" authority="Grenier" authorityName="Grenier" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="590" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subnivale">
Hieracium 
<normalizedToken id="8ACD3BCBD3381135C53F63E291B9D328" originalValue="subnivále" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">subnivale</normalizedToken>
Grenier
</taxonomicName>
u. Godron
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BA4BA6AF49012736CDA058E5082C5295" pageId="null" pageNumber="590" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="0AA8B868A04425C85254486E700D605F" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Schnee-Habichtskraut</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="301EE7E0FAC9BD3E2F8E9497FBC3E4A7" pageId="null" pageNumber="590" type="description">
<paragraph id="2D804E29958ABF502658D1EEB03F5F47" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">
5-20 cm hoch. Stengel mit 0-2 kleinen 
<normalizedToken id="376401FA72E89CB72D472056721555C9" originalValue="Stengelblättern" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Stengelblaettern</normalizedToken>
, gerade, meist 1 
<normalizedToken id="FE75B0D1F72AF69CDF24C4DB00D80824" originalValue="köpfig" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">koepfig</normalizedToken>
, fast nur im obern Teil mit 
<normalizedToken id="4E56C7F0FBB247C9219C16C7F3007D4E" originalValue="weißen" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">weissen</normalizedToken>
bis grauen, einfachen Haaren und 0,2-0,6 mm langen 
<normalizedToken id="71C8E18432B975C8952E186B2D9448EB" originalValue="Drüsenhaaren" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Druesenhaaren</normalizedToken>
. Die 
<normalizedToken id="77F494A372752E717EFEE264A43F83BD" originalValue="größeren" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">groesseren</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="4A0838FCA3F45288A4385E6567AA5095" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="7B91A9619F1C5269FE28ACB72935EFE4" originalValue="3½" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">31/2</normalizedToken>
-8mal so lang wie breit, 
<emphasis id="E337928E328D4DF2453BF60B645FD435" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">auf der Oberseite gegen die Basis zu mit zahlreichen, 6</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="54CD65C4F362FD161083593D4F8D622D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">
10 mm langen, einfachen Haaren, sonst kahl, ohne 
<normalizedToken id="48DA99263606E2D3AE7F1B328EF006D3" originalValue="Drüsenhaare" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Druesenhaare</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="D90379F7BE98107CEB353CEB65B41740" originalValue="blaugrün" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">blaugruen</normalizedToken>
.
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="3C0777174CA2CB82AEE82277CAD37D08" originalValue="Stengelblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Stengelblaetter</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="D72F74632304BC39BFEE035B581A8AE1" originalValue="Hülle" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Huelle</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="0E6169DD126EE83DF97B739D83497567" originalValue="Blüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Blueten</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="37414BB859CB9F7DF8627295F257D412" originalValue="Früchte" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Fruechte</normalizedToken>
wie bei 
<taxonomicName id="7706FAB4E55BAF039615130F05453E9D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="590" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glanduliferum">
<emphasis id="DDEDC65E127EA10A897AFE87E1149382" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">H. glanduliferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 6b). - 
<normalizedToken id="C679DD2223668DF62C50CB7D60A8B45D" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="59E6E04CFB280639B3385D1851D58D34" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis id="1E7AB45A8FE2E9441DA748AD4DCC0C11" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Zytologische Angaben.</emphasis>
Keine Untersuchungen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9F979041BE009202C2508BE04D93466F" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis id="92D0408ACCC79D8CA3C6B461D46A6A4C" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Standort.</emphasis>
Alpin. Steinige 
<normalizedToken id="58448D6101A9B504A873F88B2B2340F9" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Boeden</normalizedToken>
. Lockere Rasen, Felsen, 
<normalizedToken id="5810B50615202FCE6810A668B0D2F9FD" originalValue="Geröll" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Geroell</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="89A8F633390117988050BCD6B67AAC89" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis id="654E3860A58613DD495A78D5B4737E6E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Verbreitung. Westalpen-Pflanze:</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="9B07FA0B4F8D06E352491F3AE9C4A787" originalValue="Nordwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Nordwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Savoyen. - Im Gebiet: Maurienne (Galibier, Mont Cenis, Col de 1 
<normalizedToken id="2DC6CF5C7FB6B25344D851549EB89901" originalValue="’Iséran" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">'Iseran</normalizedToken>
, oberstes Tal von Bonneval 
<normalizedToken id="FCABE5D07F738DF0AEDBC93255496809" originalValue="aufwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">aufwaerts</normalizedToken>
), Tarentaise (
<normalizedToken id="577F33CA7630170CB74270A62B423BB1" originalValue="Vallée" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Vallee</normalizedToken>
des Allues), Mer de Glace (?); Angaben aus dem Wallis (von Gondo im Simplongebiet und von den Alpes de Fully) sind sehr zweifelhaft.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
